-- int_deduped_returns.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate returns to one approved return per item
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        item_id,
        return_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY
                CASE WHEN status = 'approved' THEN 0 ELSE 1 END,
                return_date DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
)
SELECT
    item_id,
    return_id,
    return_date,
    reason,
    status
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- fct_return_rates_by_category.sql
```sql
-- Calculate product return rates by category
WITH item_metrics AS (
    SELECT
        oi.item_id,
        oi.quantity,
        COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)') AS category_name,
        CASE WHEN dr.item_id IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS is_returned
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_products') }} p
        ON p.product_id = oi.product_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
        ON c.category_id = p.category_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} dr
        ON dr.item_id = oi.item_id
)
SELECT
    category_name,
    COUNT(*) AS total_items_sold,
    SUM(is_returned) AS total_items_returned,
    CAST(SUM(is_returned) AS DECIMAL(10,2)) / COUNT(*) AS return_rate
FROM item_metrics
GROUP BY category_name
ORDER BY return_rate DESC
